The paper deals with semi-supervised node classification in attributed graphs, which is a problem in machine learning and data mining. The paper proposes a new model for this problem, which involves graph convolutional networks (GCNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since GCNs are commonly used in these areas. The paper also involves analyzing the representation capacity of existing models, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
